[We thank John for his comment.
It is important to bear in mind that highly pathogenic influenza viruses such as the Asian H5N1 cause severe disease in most bird species. Therefore, only the few species that suffer long subclinical viremia would be able to migrate and carry it to novel regions. In the case of H5N1, these species would mainly be some ducks in the Genus _Anas_ and focus should be placed on them or other Anseriformes. The northern pintail (_Anas acuta_ sp.) has been found to migrate between North America and Asia. - Mod.PMB]

[Regarding the map,
http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_crPBWW0i46s/TU8FlLI8qQI/AAAAAAAABGI/0rSSCUp8T4g/s1600/World+Bird+Migration.jpgit
is probably intended to be indicative of the flyway origins and destinations rather than showing actual GPS locations. - Mod.JW]
